@startuml class_diagram_interactive_input

title Calculator Class and Interactive Input Architecture

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

class Calculator {
    .. Binary Arithmetic ..
    + add(a, b) : int|float
    + subtract(a, b) : int|float
    + multiply(a, b) : int|float
    + divide(a, b) : float
    + power(base, exponent) : int|float
    .. Unary Operations ..
    + factorial(n) : int
    + square(x) : int|float
    + cube(x) : int|float
    + square_root(x) : float
    + cube_root(x) : float
    + log10(x) : float
    + ln(x) : float
}

class "__main__ module" as Main {
    + main() : None
    - _parse_number(raw: str) : int|float
}

note right of Main
  Registry: dict[str, tuple[Callable, int]]
  Maps operation name -> (method, arity)
  e.g. "add" -> (calc.add, 2)
       "factorial" -> (calc.factorial, 1)
end note

Main *--> Calculator : creates (composition)
Main --> Calculator : dispatches via registry

Main ..> Main : _parse_number() called\nfor each operand prompt

@enduml
